  • Constructor Details

    • Event

      public Event()
      Default constructor for Event. Often used to create an event shell where we can then populate from a document, or for creating events when we only actually care about the ID, for navigation purposes.

    • Event

      public Event(String id, String name, String location, LocalDateTime startTime, LocalDateTime endTime, String details, ArrayList<Integer> milestones, boolean trackLocation, String organizerId, Long signUpLimit, Long lastMilestone)
      Constructor for all non-photo attributes (photos are initialized via default constructor)
      Parameters:
      id - unique ID number for event
      name - name of event
      location - location of event
      startTime - date and time (year, month, day, hour, minute) of event start
      endTime - date and time (year, month, day, hour, minute) of event end
      details - paragraph of event details
      milestones - list of attendance milestones to track
      trackLocation - is location tracking of check-ins enabled
      organizerId - the id of the organizer who created the event
      signUpLimit - number of signups for event allowed (-1 for no limit)
      lastMilestone - the last milestone that was achieved

    • Event

      public Event(String id, String name, String location, LocalDateTime startTime, LocalDateTime endTime, String details, ArrayList<Integer> milestones, String checkInQRID, String promoQRID, boolean trackLocation, List<String> checkedInAttendees, String organizerId, List<String> signedUpAttendees, Long signUpLimit, Long lastMilestone, List<Notification> notifications)
      Constructor for all attributes
      Parameters:
      id - unique ID number for event
      name - name of event
      location - location of event
      startTime - date and time (year, month, day, hour, minute) of event start
      endTime - date and time (year, month, day, hour, minute) of event end
      details - paragraph of event details
      milestones - list of attendance milestones to track
      checkInQRID - ID of QR code used to check user in to event
      promoQRID - id of QR code used to promote the event
      trackLocation - is location tracking of check-ins enabled
      checkedInAttendees - list of checked in attendees
      organizerId - the id of the organizer who created the event
      signedUpAttendees - list of signed up attendees
      signUpLimit - number of signups for event allowed (-1 for no limit)
      lastMilestone - the last milestone that was achieved
      notifications - list of notifications
